()5️⃣ ProvisioningProject:-
Ye ek ya multiple provisioning plans ka container hai.
Enterprise me bulk provisioning ya workflow ke liye use hota hai.

()ProjectType SailPoint me ek enum hai jo define karta hai ki ProvisioningProject ka type kya hai.
Ye basically batata hai ki project kya kaam karega(add karna, remove karna, ya sync karna).

()ProjectType ke values:-
Value	                                Purpose
Provision-----Identity ko naya access add karna ya modify karna. Example: nayi role assign karna.
Deprovision---Identity se access remove karna. Example: employee resign ho gaya → roles/accounts remove karna.
Reconcile-----
Reconcile = Sync karna
SailPoint me ye check karta hai ki user ke current access(roles/accounts) actual system ke state ke saath
match karte hain ya nahi.Matlab agar kisi ne manually system me role add/remove kiya,
SailPoint me abhi tak reflect(dikhna) nahi hua → Reconcile se correct ho jata hai.

2️⃣ Kaam kya karta hai?
Step	                                       Explanation
Fetch actual state-------------Application me user ke current roles/accounts fetch karta hai.
Compare with SailPoint---------SailPoint me identity ke roles/accounts jo stored hain unse compare karta hai.
Create plan------------------Agar koi mismatch hai → provisioning plan generate hota hai to add/remove access.
Execute	Plan-------------------apply hota hai, SailPoint ka data aur actual system sync ho jata hai.

Example Usage:-
// Create a provisioning project to add access
ProvisioningProject project = new ProvisioningProject(ProvisioningProject.ProjectType.Provision, context);

// Create another project to remove access
ProvisioningProject deprovisionProject = new ProvisioningProject(ProvisioningProject.ProjectType.Deprovision, context);

// Reconcile project example
ProvisioningProject reconcileProject = new ProvisioningProject(ProvisioningProject.ProjectType.Reconcile, context);
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
()👉 Real IdentityIQ me tum kabhi direct Provision use nahi karte
✔ Correct aur standard way sirf ye hai:-
Provisioner p = new Provisioner(context);
p.execute(plan);

🔹 3. Step-by-step samajh:-
🟢 Step 1: Tum plan banate ho
ProvisioningPlan plan = new ProvisioningPlan();
plan.setIdentity(identity);
👉 Matlab:-
➡️ “Is user ke liye kuch karna hai”

🟡 Step 2: Tum execute karte ho:-
Provisioner p = new Provisioner(context);
p.execute(plan);

🔵 Step 3: System internally kya karta hai:-
👉 Yaha magic hota hai:-
ProvisioningPlan
   ↓ (process / compile)
ProvisioningProject (auto ban gaya)
   ↓
Execution start

🔹 4. ProvisioningProject kyu zaroori hai? 🤔
👉 Kyunki tumhara plan simple hota hai:
Example:-
"AD me account create karo"
👉 Lekin system ko chahiye:-
✔ Kaunsa connector use hoga
✔ Account exist karta hai ya nahi
✔ Pehle kya hoga (create ya update)
✔ Kaunse attributes jayenge
✔ Dependencies kya hain
👉 Isliye system bolta hai:-
"Ruk bhai, main isko proper structure me convert karta hoon"
👉 Ye converted structure = ProvisioningProject

✅ Provisioner kya hai?
👉 Ye actual engine hai
Provisioner.execute(plan);
✔ Ye hi real execution karta hai.

✅ ProvisioningProject kya hai?
👉 Ye:-
System khud banata hai
Tum nahi banate
Ye execution-ready version hai plan ka.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
🔹 Question:-
👉 ProvisioningProject ko admin/developer banata hai ya system?

🔹 ✅ Final Answer (IMPORTANT):-
👉 ProvisioningProject ko na admin banata hai na developer
👉 ✔ Ye automatically system (IdentityIQ engine) banata hai.
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
()

ProvisioningProject =
👉 “Kaise create hoga, kis system me, kya values jayengi”

✔ ProvisioningPlan = idea
✔ProvisioningProject = execution blueprint
✔provisioner = execute(plan)

🔹 Ek line me difference 🔥:-
👉 ProvisioningProject = “kya aur kaise hoga” (plan ready)
👉 Provisioner = “kaam karke dikha” (execute karta hai).

🔹 1. ProvisioningProject kya karta hai? 🧠
👉 Ye ek data structure / object hai
✔ Plan ko process karta hai
✔ Execution ke liye ready banata hai
✔ Sab details rakhta hai

👉 Example:-
- Kis user ke liye
- Kis application me
- Kya action (create / modify)
- Kaunse attributes
👉 Matlab:-
➡️ Ye sirf instructions ka bundle hai

🔹 2. Provisioner kya karta hai? ⚙️
👉 Ye ek engine / executor class hai
Provisioner p = new Provisioner(context);
p.execute(plan);
✔ Ye actual kaam karta hai
✔ Connector ko call karta hai
✔ Target system update karta hai

()🔹 1. ProvisioningProject kya hai?
👉 ProvisioningProject = ProvisioningPlan ka processed (final) version
📌 Matlab:-
👉 Tumne jo plan diya (kya karna hai)
👉 System usko tod ke, samajh ke, ready karta hai execution ke liye
➡️ Ye readymade structure = ProvisioningProject jo execution ka blueprint.
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
🔹 4. ProvisioningProject karta kya hai? ⚙️
👉 Ye sirf data hold nahi karta — ye smart processing bhi karta hai
✔ Main kaam:-

()🔹 1. ✅ Plan ko validate karta hai:-
👉 System check karta hai:-
Identity exist karta hai ya nahi
Application (AD) exist karta hai ya nahi
Required fields diye hain ya nahi.

💡 Example:-
❌ Galat case:-
User: unknown.user
Application: AD

👉 Result:-
Error: Identity not found

✔ Sahi case:-
john.doe exist karta hai → OK
------------------------------------
🔹 2. ✅ Application-wise todta hai:-
👉 Agar multiple applications hain, system unko separate karta hai
💡 Example:-
1. AD me account create
2. SAP me role assign
👉 System internally banata hai:-
AD → AccountRequest
SAP → AccountRequest
✔ Har application ka alag processing
--------------------------------------
🔹 3. ✅ Dependencies set karta hai 🔗
👉 Kaunsa kaam pehle aur baad me hoga
💡 Example:-
1. Account create
2. Role assign
👉 Dependency:-
Create → then Assign Role
❌ Galat order:-
Role assign pehle → fail (account exist nahi karta)
✔ System correct order set karta hai.
----------------------------------------
🔹 4. ✅ Actions organize karta hai,
👉 Sab actions ko clean structure me arrange karta hai
💡 Example:-
Tumne diya:-
email update
role assign
account create
👉 System organize karega:-
Step 1: Account create
Step 2: Email set
Step 3: Role assign
✔ Logical grouping karta hai

🔹 5. ✅ Execution order decide karta hai ⚙️
👉 Final sequence banata hai execution ke liye
💡 Example final flow:-
Step 1 → AD me account create
Step 2 → Attributes set (email etc.)
Step 3 → Role assign
👉 Ye hi order Provisioner follow karega.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
🔹 5. ProvisioningProject ke andar kya kya hota hai? 🧠
--🔸 1. Identity:-
👉 Kis user ke liye provisioning ho raha hai
Example: john.doe

🔸 2. AccountRequests 🔥 (MOST IMPORTANT):-
👉 Har application ke liye request
- AD → create account
- SAP → modify role
✔ Har AccountRequest me hota hai:
application
nativeIdentity
operation (Create / Modify / Delete)

🔸 3. ObjectRequests:-
👉 Groups / roles / entitlements ke changes
Example:
Add user to group "Admin"

🔸 4. AttributeRequests:-
👉 Actual field changes
email = new@mail.com
role = Admin

🔸 5. ProvisioningTargets:-
👉 Kaun kaun se systems involved hain
AD, SAP, DB

🔸 6. Dependencies 🔗:-
👉 Execution order decide karta hai
Account create → then role assign

🔸 7. Result / Status:-
👉 Execution ke baad kya hua
SUCCESS / FAILED / PARTIAL

🔸 8. Errors / Messages:-
👉 Agar kuch fail hua toh reason
"Account already exists"
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
